# Astro Component Guidelines

## Component Structure

Astro components have a frontmatter section (between ---) for imports, props, and logic,
followed by the template section with HTML and Astro expressions.

### Standard Pattern

1. Imports at the top
2. Props interface (TypeScript)
3. Destructure props with defaults
4. Data fetching / logic
5. Template with slots

## File Organization

- src/components/layout/ - Layout components (Header, Footer, Layout)
- src/components/marketing/ - Marketing sections (Hero, FeatureGrid, CTASection)
- src/components/islands/ - React interactive components

## Slots

Use <slot /> for default content, <slot name="xyz" /> for named slots.
Children use slot="xyz" attribute or <Fragment slot="xyz"> wrapper.

## Static vs Dynamic

- Static (default): No client JS shipped
- Dynamic: Use React islands with client:visible, client:load, client:idle

## Content Collections

Use getCollection from astro:content for typed content queries.

## SEO

Define title, description, canonical URL in frontmatter and render in head.
